<paragraph blockId="17.[151,855,1962,2028]" box="[151,408,2002,2028]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">(Sahelian Tree locust)</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,151,738]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,281,151,177]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Occurs" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1764" box="[581,735,152,177]" class="Insecta" family="Baissogryllidae" genus="Anacridium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aegyptium">
<emphasis box="[581,735,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">A. aegyptium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in general appearance but distinguishable by its light brown colour, broadly obtuse-angular pronotum with rounded apex, hind wing basally light pink or yellow, with a short dark narrow median basal fascia, not covering entire hind wing.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,151,738]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,314,271,297]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Habitats:</emphasis>
The usual habitat is xerophilous open woodland, the trees and shrubs. The natural food plants are various trees, especially 
<emphasis box="[480,616,312,337]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicName box="[480,612,312,337]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Acacia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spp">Acacia spp</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[673,889,312,337]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicName box="[673,884,312,337]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Capparaceae" genus="Capparis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Capparales" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="decidua">Capparis decidua</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Also recorded feeding on Sorghum and herbaceous plants. Young hoppers feed on grasses but later stages, like adults are arborivorous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
