<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,151,738]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,321,671,697]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Remarks:</emphasis>
This species is known as Sahelian Tree Locust. It was recorded from Libyan Desert by 
<bibRefCitation author="Shaw, W. B. K." pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="174 - 177" refId="ref30692" refString="Shaw, W. B. K. (1933) Insects and other Arthropods Collected by Major R. A. Bagnold's expedition to the Libyan Desert. Entomologist, 66, 174 - 177." type="journal article" year="1933">Shaw (1933)</bibRefCitation>
. This monimate subspecies is recorded for the first time from Fezzan.
</paragraph>
